{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Me3xvkPyE4GLf2eAL9apxK","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t## F2 – TCP vs HTTP port mismatch for `./clickhouse client --port`\n2\t\n3\t`CLICKHOUSE_URL` (e.g. `http://localhost:8123`) uses the HTTP port, but `./clickhouse client`\n4\tconnects via the native TCP protocol whose default port is **9000**, not 8123.\n5\t\n6\t`scripts/migrate.ts` passes whatever port appears in `CLICKHOUSE_URL` to `--port`, so a default\n7\t`CLICKHOUSE_URL` of `http://localhost:8123` will tell the client to connect on TCP port 8123, which\n8\twill fail if ClickHouse is listening on the native TCP port 9000.\n9\t\n10\t**Decision**: keep the current behaviour (pass the URL port as-is) so the env var controls the\n11\tport explicitly. Operators running a non-default setup must set `CLICKHOUSE_URL` to the native TCP\n12\tport (e.g. `http://localhost:9000`) when using `pnpm migrate`. The default local setup with the\n13\tbundled binary uses port 9000 for native TCP — adjust `CLICKHOUSE_URL` or set `--port` separately\n14\tif needed. This is an integration concern; unit tests are not affected.\n15\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7e2ac13e-0c1e-4a44-830c-fe831f6f0d29","uuid":"f7d45fda-f7ff-4ccc-9227-70ca0c35c717","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:04:59.097Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/ISSUES.md","content":"## F2 – TCP vs HTTP port mismatch for `./clickhouse client --port`\n\n`CLICKHOUSE_URL` (e.g. `http://localhost:8123`) uses the HTTP port, but `./clickhouse client`\nconnects via the native TCP protocol whose default port is **9000**, not 8123.\n\n`scripts/migrate.ts` passes whatever port appears in `CLICKHOUSE_URL` to `--port`, so a default\n`CLICKHOUSE_URL` of `http://localhost:8123` will tell the client to connect on TCP port 8123, which\nwill fail if ClickHouse is listening on the native TCP port 9000.\n\n**Decision**: keep the current behaviour (pass the URL port as-is) so the env var controls the\nport explicitly. Operators running a non-default setup must set `CLICKHOUSE_URL` to the native TCP\nport (e.g. `http://localhost:9000`) when using `pnpm migrate`. The default local setup with the\nbundled binary uses port 9000 for native TCP — adjust `CLICKHOUSE_URL` or set `--port` separately\nif needed. This is an integration concern; unit tests are not affected.\n","numLines":15,"startLine":1,"totalLines":15}}}
